<td width="50%">

### ğŸ¯ Fluent API Design
```python
import qldata as qd

# One-liner to get clean data
df = qd.data("BTCUSDT", source="binance")
    .last(30)
    .resolution("1h")
    .clean()
    .get()
```

</td>
<td width="50%">

### ğŸ“¡ Real-Time Streaming
```python
# Live data with resilience built-in
stream = qd.stream(["BTCUSDT", "ETHUSDT"])
    .resolution("tick")
    .on_data(handle_tick)
    .get(start=True)
```

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50%">

### ğŸ”„ Data Transforms
```python
# Clean, fill, and resample
clean_df = (
    qd.data("BTCUSDT", source="binance")
    .last(7)
    .resolution("1m")
    .clean(remove_outliers=True)
    .fill_forward()
    .resample("1h")
    .get()
)
```

</td>
<td width="50%">

### ğŸ›¡ï¸ Built for Reliability
```python
# Built-in monitoring & alerts
from qldata.monitoring import (
    DataQualityMonitor,
    AlertManager
)

monitor = DataQualityMonitor()
alerts = AlertManager()
alerts.on_stale_data(send_alert)
```

